					Week 10 (odd calendar week)
				


CTU  FEE  Students  Introduction to PhD studies



Introduction to PhD studies
At the Faculty of Electrical Engineering at CTU you could specialize in 16 different branches of study. The faculty offers PhD programmes in broad range of fields in electrical engineering and information technology. All study programs are closely linked with research. We collaborate extensively with other universities and institutions worldwide. Our goal is to prepare doctoral students for successful scientific and/or other career. By receiving higher qualifications that includes the knowledge of foreign languages, our PhD graduates are in high demand at job market.
Our PhD programme consists of:

an independent scientific work
presentations at international academic conferences
publications in influential journals
teaching activities and examinations
study abroad
PhD thesis and its public defense
More information can be found here.



				Responsible person: 
				RNDr. Patrik Mottl, Ph.D.







